Clarify what kind of unit it is. Planck is probably best known for the unit of length, known (somewhat incorrectly) as a fundamental lower bound, and some of his other units (such as Planck temperature) also constitute some boundary. His unit of mass, however, has no such purpose so that should be noted.

/* History */ Vague reference to "shortest time possible". What it means "many scientists". And in what sense they mean it to be shortest time possible. There is no theory really suggesting what thos that mean. Removed.
